<p><strong>Butler doesnt end when you graduate! </strong></p><p>Butler has a thriving alumni community that puts on annual reunions back in Durham and London, hosts sporting events and provide a platform to help current students! Just to name a few things the community does!</p><p>You can keep involved in the Butler alumni community easily, using the social media links on the right.&nbsp; There are a range of Butler&nbsp;alumni events across the country, so make sure&nbsp;to try some out.&nbsp;</p><p>For those that have left Butler, make sure that you aren't left out of the loop by updating the details that college hold for you <a href="http://www.dur.ac.uk/butler.college/alumni/">here</a>.</p><p>Please browse the JCR website too to see what's going on!&nbsp; If you would like to make a donation to the College, you can do so online through the Josephine Butler College Trust - <a href="https://www.dunelm.org.uk/sslpage.aspx?pid=356">https://www.dunelm.org.uk/sslpage.aspx?pid=356</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>If you have any questions, please call&nbsp;Alice Whitehouse, Alumni&nbsp;Relations Assistant, on 0191 334 7264 or get in touch using the&nbsp;links to the right.</p><h2>Butler Angels</h2><h3>If you are an Alum</h3><p>If you are not an Angel, why not&nbsp;<a href="http://www.dur.ac.uk/butler.angels">become one today?</a>&nbsp;It's a simple way to help out current Butlerites in the competitive job market.</p><h3>If you are a current student</h3><p>Why not&nbsp;<a href="http://www.dur.ac.uk/butler.angels">contact an Angel?</a>&nbsp;It is important to think about what you want to do beyond your time at Butler and Durham. The Angels are alumni and friends of the College who have volunteered to help YOU as you look to your future. Whether you know what you want to do and would like some advice on applications and interviews, or you have no idea, have a browse of the Angels site. It takes seconds to email an Angel through the website. They would love to help you.</p><h2>Moles! New For 2015!</h2><p><img src="http://butlerjcr.co.uk/application/views/alumni/img/upload/001.jpg" alt="" /></p><h3>How to order?</h3><p>Email <a href="mailto:jbalumni.association@durham.ac.uk">jbalumni.association@durham.ac.uk</a>&nbsp;if you would like to order a mole, please include Name and Delivery Address.</p><p>They cost &pound;17.50 (+&pound;3.50 P+P). You will then recieve a reply email stating how to pay, you can either pay through a bank transfer or through cheque. When the payment has been recieved the mole will be posted to you.</p><p>All proceeds go towards the Josephine Butler College Trust Fund.</p>